experiencing some growing pains these days. been finding ways to step back in life and really take stock of all the old ways of being that don’t serve me anymore. here are some moments that have made my heart sing recently. but mostly i’ve been in a deep sea of change, health struggles, and an emotional rut that’s lasted a bit longer than i’m used to. but i’m learning you can’t place a timeline on feeling your feelings. or rush through deep transformation. i’m learning to be grateful for the shadows, the in between, the metamorphosis. what a gift that i get to feel all of the things!! just wanted to pop on and say don’t ignore your body. don’t ignore your heart. it talks to you and you’ll hear it if you just get quiet enough. it’s okay to disappear for a while and tend to your needs. i’m playing a festival tomorrow and i haven’t stepped on a stage in a minute and i’m feeling all types of ways about being seen in a vulnerable state. but i’ve never been one for a facade. if you see me, please air hug me from afar. this pisces is fragile at the moment but her soul and love for life, in all its glory and gore, do be strong 🤍

fletcher & her friends 2023

fletchfam! my heart is so happy to announce i’ve partnered with @tinder for MEET HER AT THE BAR year two.

it was one of the most fulfilling experiences of my career to date launching our pride experience last year in support of the incredible bars across the country that The Lesbian Project introduced me to.

my heart is so happy to continue lifting up the spaces where we can love each other a little harder. some of your local woman-owned queer bars will be hosting their own FLETCHER-themed nights throughout the month and i can't wait to celebrate with you IRL at Nashville’s Lipstick Lounge on June 25. i am so excited for you to meet up with your friends and to make new ones this Pride (or even to meet your Tinder crush for the first time)! 

we have some fun surprises and prizes for you + you’ll be able to find exclusive merch available at each bar and online today (with 100% net proceeds to each of these small businesses who need us now more than ever.)

last year we raised $50K for @glaad (!!!) in support of the amazing work they do and i hope we can double that # and more this year. donate now here on my IG or by purchasing an official MEET HER AT THE BAR t-shirt today at the link in my bio 🤍

headlined nashville pride last night. it was hot as hell and we had technical issues like no other, but it i felt so at home in the space we created of sexy, sweaty, sapphic energy to kick off our summer. thank you all for showing up for me and being your unapologetic selves. it was an honor do that with you all. we will not dim our light for anyone else but continue to express ourselves as who we are, pure love. 

the fun continues tonight — @the_lipstick_lounge is hosting their Meet Her At The Bar night from 6pm onwards (open to the public, limited capacity) 👄 proceeds of our t-shirts go directly to supporting this beautiful bar & proceeds from my Instagram campaign go directly to @GLAAD ❣️

fammm. what a dream celebrating year 2 of #meetheratthebar with a surprise appearance at the iconic @the_lipstick_lounge in Nashville after a special evening with @tinder & some of the Fletch Fam to cap off our incredible Pride weekend. thank you to everyone who’s shown up and supported one of your local bars’ FLETCHER nights this month and to those who have already donated to @GLAAD. we’re on track to raise more than double our donation for 2022. a few more days to purchase a t-shirt or to contribute @ meetheratthebar.com 🫶🏼

headlining pride in nashville was a dream. thank you @postmates for being there to celebrate with us by helping support @glaad at the festival and Meet Her At The Bar. my heart is still so full from you all showing up, being yourselves and singing your hearts out with me. #postmatespartner

Fletch Fam in Europe! 1 month until TRIP OF MY DREAMS. come spend the week with me on a beautiful island off Portugal. i’ll be doing a couple intimate performances just for you, drinking tequila with you, and there will be pool parties, excursions, dinners… it’s something i’ve never done before and i wanted to find a way  to go on a ~holiday~ with you bbs. we were able to get all new package options added (starting at $250) if you can join me. all the info in my bio link. see you soon 💓✨

fletchfam!!! i am so proud of us and honored to announce that in year 2 of #MeetHerAtTheBar we have raised nearly $150k for @glaad (3x last year) in addition to spotlighting and supporting 15 of the remaining woman-owned queer bars around the country. so grateful to our presenting sponsor @tinder for helping bring our 2023 campaign to life with me alongside my team at @capitolrecords and @teamrogue; @thelesbianbarproject for inspiring our mission; @fletcherxfinding for assisting our fan events across the country; @the_lipstick_lounge for letting me crash their fletcher night after nashville pride; @postmates, @jdsportsus, @iheartradio, @lyft, @bellesaco, @kobaltmusic, @eastgoesglobal + more for their generous donations; and of course all of you for purchasing our exclusive merchandise and for showing up to your local bars in support of their businesses and our cause. this is one of the most impactful things i’ve ever done in my career, so thank you for believing in it as much as i do ❤️‍🔥 for those who would still like to donate, please visit glaad.org. for those of you who missed this year, see you in 2024 x
